This paper is about implementing matrix decompositions as differentiable operators in deep learning systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of these operators in learning Gaussian process and Bayesian linear regression models, which are topics related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GPU acceleration for the implementation, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of these operators for Kalman smoothing, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY).
